    • lookupParticipant

      public DomainParticipant lookupParticipant(int domainId)
      Description copied from class: DomainParticipantFactory
      This operation retrieves a previously created DomainParticipant belonging to specified domain ID. If no such DomainParticipant exists, the operation will return null. If multiple DomainParticipant entities belonging to that domain ID exist, then the operation will return one of them. It is not specified which one.
      Specified by:
      lookupParticipant in class DomainParticipantFactory

    • setQos

      public void setQos(DomainParticipantFactoryQos qos)
      Description copied from class: DomainParticipantFactory
      This operation sets the value of the DomainParticipantFactory QoS policies. These policies control the behavior of the object, a factory for entities. Note that despite having QoS, the DomainParticipantFactory is not an Entity.
      Specified by:

    • getDefaultParticipantQos

      public DomainParticipantQos getDefaultParticipantQos()
      Description copied from class: DomainParticipantFactory
      This operation retrieves the default value of the DomainParticipant QoS, that is, the QoS policies which will be used for newly created DomainParticipant entities in the case where the QoS policies are defaulted in the DomainParticipantFactory.createParticipant() operation. The values retrieved will match the set of values specified on the last successful call to DomainParticipantFactory.setDefaultParticipantQos(DomainParticipantQos), or else, if the call was never made, the default values identified by the DDS specification.
      Specified by:
      getDefaultParticipantQos in class DomainParticipantFactory
      See Also:
      • DomainParticipantFactory.setDefaultParticipantQos(DomainParticipantQos)
